race.comment: We kick off a tough Oaks day with a wide-open race. FULL HAO (12) looks well placed to peak here for the lethal Waller/J-Mac combination. Two runs back in Sydney have been rock solid and she'll be better for them up to 1700m on the big track. FIRST CHORUS (11) is a progressive type who stuck on well at Geelong as favourite last time for second. The run prior behind a progressive type was good and with any luck from the wide gate she'll take beating. REALIKA (14) is knocking on the door with consecutive minor placings, good to the line at Sandown Hillside last time. The placing behind Surfin' Bird prior reads well. HOUSE OF LORDS (13) is a lightly raced mare who can bounce back off a disappointing run when firmly in the market at Pakenham.
